# Sales Import Application

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env.local` file in the root directory:

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
N8N_WEBHOOK_URL=https://xyz.brightyindonesia.com/webhook-test/ceed4c48-1970-46e8-af3d-806eee9ba3f3
NODE_ENV=development
```

For production (Vercel):
- Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` to your production URL
- Set `N8N_WEBHOOK_URL` to your n8n webhook URL

## Development

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Visit `http://localhost:3000` in your browser.

## Build & Deploy

### For Vercel:
1. Push your code to GitHub
2. Connect repository to Vercel
3. Add environment variables in Vercel dashboard
4. Deploy automatically

### For Self-Hosted Server:
```bash
npm run build
npm start
```

The app will be available at `http://your-server:3000`
